The paper deals with the performance limits of Compressed Sensing matrices, specifically in terms of the Restricted Isometry property. This falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also makes use of geometric insights and techniques, which suggests a possible fit under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and numerical analysis, which could place it under the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes simulations, which could potentially place it under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
